subject: Xylem
description: Xylem is a vital tissue found in vascular plants that plays a crucial role in the transport of water and nutrients from the roots to the rest of the plant. It is typically located within the stem and is essential for maintaining the plant's structure and health. This tissue is composed of specialized cells that facilitate the movement of fluids, contributing to the overall growth and vitality of the plant. In addition to its transport functions, xylem also provides support, enabling plants to reach great heights and thrive in various environments.
